        "summary":  "The Linux Foundation announced the Agent Name Service (ANS) framework, which applies DNS-style federated identity and discovery to AI agents, allowing enterprises to publish and verify agent identities through domains they already control without relying on proprietary registries. ANS incorporates Decentralised Identifiers and Legal Entity Identifiers to mitigate DNS\u0027s inherent spoofing vulnerabilities.",
