        "execSummary":  "This piece is a strategic prompt for enterprise leaders: AI tools alone deliver marginal ROI; the real competitive lever is the system of governance, security, and orchestration running underneath them. Microsoft frames its own integrated platform as the answer, but the underlying argument holds regardless of vendor ΓÇö your AI investment is only as strong as the infrastructure managing it. Customer-support leaders should audit whether their AI deployments have production-grade oversight or are still running as isolated pilots. The call to action is moving from experimentation to trusted, governed, end-to-end agentic systems.",
