        "execSummary":  "Brad Smith\u0027s essay signals that even inside Microsoft, the human-impact narrative around AI is escalating ΓÇö this is no longer just an R\u0026D conversation. For enterprise leaders, the strategic implication is that AI transformation must be paired with workforce investment and change management, or it will generate internal resistance and external regulatory scrutiny. Customer-support organizations, where entry-level roles are most exposed, should treat workforce reskilling as a parallel workstream to AI deployment. The vendor-positive framing is light here; the underlying workforce dynamics are genuine and worth taking seriously.",
