        "summary":  "Stripe deployed a production AI agent system on AWS using Amazon Bedrock that reduced financial compliance review time by 26 percent while maintaining human oversight throughout the process. The system uses a ReAct agent framework with task decomposition, dedicated infrastructure, and prompt caching to achieve over 96 percent helpfulness ratings. Human experts retain control of all final decisions, with the agent handling research, synthesis, and first-pass analysis.",
        "execSummary":  "Stripe\u0027s compliance agent is one of the most concrete enterprise AI production case studies available: quantified time savings, a named helpfulness metric, and an explicit human-in-the-loop design. For customer-support and operations leaders, the 26% time reduction and 96% helpfulness benchmark are the kind of measurable outcomes needed to justify AI investment to boards and regulators. The human-oversight model also provides a compliance-ready blueprint for deploying agents in regulated environments without ceding audit control. Treat this as a reference architecture for enterprise agent deployments, with the caveat that Stripe\u0027s scale and engineering maturity may not reflect your organization\u0027s starting point.",
