        "theme":  "Orchestration",
        "summary":  "AWS presents agentic overlays ΓÇö thin wrapper layers that transform legacy REST APIs into Agent-to-Agent compatible services without requiring a full rebuild of existing systems. Two implementation patterns are described: within-application overlays and AWS Bedrock AgentCore Gateway deployments, both preserving existing business logic. The approach enables legacy enterprise services to participate in modern multi-agent orchestration architectures incrementally.",
        "execSummary":  "The retrofit-vs-rebuild framing directly addresses the most common enterprise AI adoption blocker: organizations cannot justify the risk or cost of re-platforming core systems just to enable AI agents. Agentic overlays offer a pragmatic migration path ΓÇö wrap what exists, preserve what works, and unlock AI orchestration without a big-bang transformation. For IT and operations leaders, this lowers the time-to-value curve and reduces change management scope significantly. AWS naturally recommends its own Bedrock AgentCore Gateway as the preferred deployment path, so evaluate the vendor dependency against your cloud strategy.",
