        "execSummary":  "Cara\u0027s 10-hours-per-user-per-week time savings is one of the strongest per-seat efficiency metrics in enterprise AI to date, and it comes from a vertical-specific build rather than a general-purpose deployment. For leaders evaluating AI in regulated back-office functions, this case study underscores the value of domain-tuned models and workflows over generic chatbot deployments. The AWS-native architecture (EKS + Bedrock) is a useful reference for organizations already in the AWS ecosystem. As with all vendor case studies, validate the claims independently and assess whether insurance brokerage workflow complexity maps to your own operational environment.",
