        "execSummary":  "The NVIDIA-AWS infrastructure announcement matters to enterprise leaders because production AI costs are dominated by inference compute ΓÇö and a 4.6x performance improvement per GPU generation directly translates to lower cost-per-query at scale. For organizations running or planning RAG-based AI applications, GPU-accelerated vector search in OpenSearch Serverless removes a key bottleneck in the retrieval pipeline. The Exemplar Cloud designation is primarily a marketing credential, but the underlying compute improvements are real and should factor into capacity planning for 2026-2027 AI infrastructure contracts. Evaluate total cost of ownership across the full G7 instance family before committing to long-term reserved capacity.",
