        "summary":  "CIOs face competing pressures to accelerate AI adoption while maintaining adequate governance and risk management. Leading organizations like Zuora and Hi Marley are structuring independent compliance oversight with dedicated risk teams separate from innovation functions. The article argues that building secure governance foundations is a prerequisite for sustainable AI deployment at enterprise scale.",
        "execSummary":  "For senior leaders, this article reinforces that speed-to-deploy and risk containment are not mutually exclusive ΓÇö they require structural separation rather than compromise. Organizations that embed checks between innovation and risk teams outperform peers in sustainable AI scaling. The practical takeaway: governance is architecture, not afterthought. Leaders should audit whether their AI oversight function is independent enough to catch what innovation teams miss.",
