        "summary":  "Nintex launched Orchestration and Agent Designer capabilities to help enterprises move AI agents from proof-of-concept stages into production workflows. The platform combines agentic AI with business process orchestration, enabling users to build agents natively and connect them directly into orchestration pipelines. The solution addresses the governance and scaling challenge of intelligent automation across complex business processes.",
        "execSummary":  "For enterprise and support leaders evaluating agentic platforms, this piece illustrates what production-ready AI agents actually require: native integration with process orchestration rather than bolted-on automation. The Nintex model ΓÇö agents built inside orchestration rather than alongside it ΓÇö reduces integration friction and governance gaps. Leaders should evaluate existing workflow automation vendors for agentic extensions before adding a separate agent platform, as fragmentation compounds governance risk. This is a vendor-specific but architecturally instructive example.",
