        "summary":  "An IBM study of 1,000 senior executives reveals that over 70% of business leaders find switching from their primary AI provider difficult, with nearly 68% citing data residency and sovereignty as key obstacles. Only 7% of organizations report maintaining sufficient control over their AI systems. Experts recommend multivendor strategies with common standards and transparent governance to preserve long-term adaptability.",
