        "execSummary":  "This data exposes a high-stakes paradox: enterprises are deploying autonomous AI decision-making at scale despite a fundamental trust deficit. For customer support leaders, this is especially critical ΓÇö AI agents making material decisions on cases, refunds, or escalations without sufficient trust frameworks creates both customer experience and compliance exposure. The 95% preference for internal upskilling over hiring is a meaningful signal for workforce strategy. Leaders should establish explicit AI decision-authority matrices that define which decisions AI can make autonomously versus which require human confirmation.",
