        "summary":  "A Protiviti survey of over 850 global executives reveals a confidence gap in AI\u0027s business value, with 61% of CIOs believing AI drives revenue growth compared to fewer than one-third of CEOs. Organizations with greater AI maturity and stronger C-suite alignment on success metrics report better performance outcomes. Experts recommend shared governance frameworks, clear KPIs, and regular business-focused communication to bridge leadership perspectives.",
        "execSummary":  "The CEO-CIO confidence gap on AI ROI is not a communications problem ΓÇö it is a measurement problem, and this survey makes that visible at scale. For technology and support leaders making the case for AI investment, the implication is clear: AI value must be expressed in business outcomes (revenue, retention, cost per resolution), not technical metrics. Leaders who own AI programs should proactively co-design success metrics with their CEOs before presenting AI roadmaps, not after. Shared governance frameworks that include both business and IT leadership in metric design are the structural fix.",
