        "summary":  "The Linux Foundation is developing an open Agent Name Service standard built on DNS infrastructure to enable enterprises to securely verify and identify AI agents operating across the internet. Only 11% of technology executives report feeling ready for the anticipated scale of agent deployment, with governance frameworks lagging significantly behind adoption rates.",
        "execSummary":  "An open agent identity standard from the Linux Foundation is a foundational infrastructure move that enterprise leaders should monitor closely ΓÇö it signals that the AI agent ecosystem is maturing toward interoperability and accountability norms. For support leaders deploying agents across vendor ecosystems, agent identity and permissioning verification will become a compliance requirement, not a nice-to-have. The 11% readiness figure is a stark benchmark: if your organization is among the 89% unprepared, the window to build governance posture before agent proliferation is narrow. Engage your security and architecture teams on agent identity frameworks now.",
